    axs[i].set_ylim(0, 1.3)
    axs[i].set_yticks([0, 0.5, 1])

fig, (ax1, ax2) = plt.subplots(nrows=2, figsize=(18, 7), sharex=True)  # Use unpacking for 2 subplots

fig.subplots_adjust(hspace=0)
xlim = [0, 20000]

# Define a color list for P1-P4
colors = ['#06C2AC', '#9A0EEA', '#FFD700', '#929591']  # You can customize these colors

# Plot each column with its corresponding color
for i, col in enumerate(df2.columns):
    if col in ['P1', 'P2', 'P3', 'P4']:
        ax1.plot(df2[col], color=colors[i], label=col)  # Use label for legend
    else:
        ax1.plot(df2[col], color='#aaaaaa')  # Use a different color for other columns

ax1.set_xlim(xlim)
ax1.set_ylim(0, 1.3)
ax1.set_yticks([0, 0.5, 1])
ax1.set_ylabel('Values', fontsize=10)
ax1.xaxis.grid(True, linestyle = 'dotted',linewidth = 2)
ax1.legend(loc = "upper left")  # Add legend for P1-P4

# Rest of the code for annotations subplot (ax2) remains the same

## code to plot annotations

ax2.set_xlabel('Genomic position', fontsize=10)
ax2.set_ylabel('Annotations', fontsize=10)
ax2.set_ylim(-0.5, 1.5)
ax2.set_yticks([0, 1])
ax2.set_yticklabels(['', '+'])
ax2.xaxis.grid(True, linestyle = 'dotted',linewidth = 2)

for _, r in df1.iterrows():
    marker = '|'
    markersize = 10
    lw = 2
    if r['type'] == 'exon':
        marker = None
        lw = 15
    y = 1 if r['strand'] == '+' else 0
    ax2.plot((r['start'], r['stop']), (y, y),
             marker=marker, lw=lw,
             solid_capstyle='butt',
             color='#505050')

In[104]:
# Step 2: Process the data
custom_labels = ['x->y', 'x->z', 'y->x', 'y->z']  # X-axis labels
labels = bp['Unnamed: 0']
condition_a_sample_1 = bp['condition_a_sample_1']
condition_a_sample_2 = bp['condition_a_sample_2']
control = bp['control']

x = np.arange(len(labels))  # the label locations
width = 0.2  # the width of the bars
spacing = 0.02

# Step 3: Plot the data
fig, ax = plt.subplots()
rects1 = ax.bar(x - (width + spacing / 2), condition_a_sample_1, width, label='Condition A Sample 1', color = 'black', zorder = 3)
rects2 = ax.bar(x, condition_a_sample_2, width, label='Condition A Sample 2',  color = 'black', zorder = 3)
rects3 = ax.bar(x + (width + spacing / 2), control, width, label='Control', color = 'red', zorder = 3)

ax.set_yticks(np.arange(0, 2725, 500))
ax.set_yticks(np.arange(0, 2725, 250), minor=True)
ax.yaxis.grid(True, which = 'major', zorder = 0, linestyle = 'dotted')
ax.yaxis.grid(True, which='minor', linestyle = 'dotted')
ax.set_ylabel('Number of events')
ax.set_xticks(x)
ax.set_xticklabels(custom_labels)
condition_patch = plt.Line2D([0], [0], color='black', lw=4, label='Condition')
control_patch = plt.Line2D([0], [0], color='red', lw=4, label='Control')
ax.legend(handles=[condition_patch, control_patch])


plt.show()
